In this file i will attach all the SQL Query. which is used in data analytic

Basic SQL Query:

Create: Used to create a new table in the database.
CREATE TABLE employees (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    position VARCHAR(50),
    salary DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

Insert: Inserts new records into a table.
INSERT INTO employees (id, name, position, salary)
VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 'Manager', 70000.00);

Update: Modifies existing records in a table.
UPDATE employees
SET salary = 75000
WHERE id = 1;

Alter: Used to modify the structure of an existing table (e.g., add a column).
ALTER TABLE employees
ADD hire_date DATE;

Delete: Remove records from table based on condition.
DELETE FROM employees
WHERE id = 1;

Drop: Deletes entire table or database
DROP TABLE employees;

Truncate: Remove all record from table, but keeps the structure.
TRUNCATE TABLE employees;
